      <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
	<p>The edition is based on <ref target="bibl:Kan">Poonacha 2013</ref> and <ref target="bibl:Falk2009">Falk 2009</ref>. The translation is AO’s, based on the translations given by Poonacha and Falk. It is clear that the gift is of an architectural element (a paṭṭa or slab).</p>
      </div>
      <div type="edition" xml:lang="mi-Latn">
	<p>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	    siddha || na<supplied reason="lost">mo</supplied>
	    bhagavato samasabudhasa <app><lem wit="#Poonacha">adholoka</lem
	      ><rdg wit="#Falk">śudhalaka</rdg></app
	      >-mahā<lb n="2" break="no"/>
	    ce<supplied reason="lost">t</supplied>iya
	    <supplied reason="lost">ra</supplied>ño
	    <persName key="pers:VpŚrīPuḷumāvi">vā<app
	      ><lem wit="#Falk">seṭhi</lem>
	       <rdg wit="#Poonacha">sithī</rdg>
	    </app><unclear>p</unclear>uta-siri-pu<app
	      ><lem wit="#Falk">lu</lem>
	       <rdg wit="#Poonacha">ḷu</rdg>
	    </app>māvisa</persName>
	  <lb n="3"/>
	    savachare <date when-custom="35"
	                    datingPoint="pers:VpŚrīPuḷumāvi"
			    datingMethod="regnal">30 5</date>
	    <unclear>gimhana pakhe</unclear> 2 10 
	    <placeName key="pl:Koruṅkala"><app><lem wit="#Falk">koruku<unclear>lana</unclear></lem
	      ><rdg wit="#Poonacha">kotujilāna</rdg></app></placeName>
	  <lb n="4"/>
	    bhikhu<app
	      ><lem wit="#Poonacha">nīya</lem
	      ><rdg wit="#Falk">niye</rdg>
	    </app> 
	    <persName key="pers:Dharmaśrī">dhamasiriyāya</persName> a<app
	      ><lem wit="#Poonacha">gatuko </lem>
	       <rdg wit="#Falk">khar<unclear>i</unclear>ka</rdg>
	    </app>pa<app
	      ><lem wit="#Falk">ṭa</lem>
	       <rdg wit="#Poonacha">tha <note xml:lang="en">(a typo for ṭa)</note></rdg>
	      </app>sa<lb n="5" break="no"/>tharo ca deyadhama 
	    sa<app><lem wit="#Falk">ha a<unclear>māpitu</unclear>hi</lem>
	           <rdg wit="#Poonacha">hā amāpi hi</rdg></app> saha ca <app
	      ><lem wit="#Falk">me</lem
	      ><rdg wit="#Poonacha">mā</rdg>
	    </app>
	  <lb n="6"/>
	    upajā<app
	      ><lem wit="#Falk">e</lem>
	       <rdg wit="#Poonacha">tha</rdg>
	    </app>hi bhayata-varana<app
	      ><lem wit="#Falk">bhu</lem>
	       <rdg wit="#Poonacha">bhū</rdg>
	    </app>tihi sa<app
	      ><lem wit="#Falk">ha</lem>
	       <rdg wit="#Poonacha">hi</rdg>
	    </app> ca bhayata
	  <lb n="7"/>
	    <unclear>s</unclear>i<app
	      ><lem wit="#Falk">he</lem>
	       <rdg wit="#Poonacha">pe</rdg>
	    </app>hi savasa<app
	      ><lem wit="#Falk"><unclear>ta</unclear></lem>
	       <rdg wit="#Poonacha">tā</rdg></app>na
	    ca hitasu<app
	      ><lem wit="#Falk">gha</lem>
	       <rdg wit="#Poonacha">ghā</rdg>
	    </app>tha
	</p>
