      <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
	<p>
	  Success! Reverence to the lord,
	  the fully enlightened one,
	  of the Great Caitya at Adholoka.
	  In the thirty-fifth year of King
	  <persName key="pers:VpŚrīPuḷumāvi">Vāsiṣṭhīputra
	    Śrī Puḷumāvi</persName>,
	  in the second half-month of summer, on the 
	  tenth day, there was a pious donation by the nun
	  <persName key="pers:Dharmaśrī">Dharmaśrī</persName>
	  of <placeName key="pl:Koruṅkala">Koruṅkala</placeName>
	  of a replacement slab-covering,
	  together with my mother and father, and together
	  with my teacher, the venerable 
	  <persName key="pers:BhVaraṇabhūti">Varaṇabhūti</persName>,
	  and together with the monk 
	  <persName key="pers:BhSiṃha">Siṃha</persName>, and
	  for the benefit and happiness of all beings.
	</p>
      </div>
